---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { siteConfig } from '../data/site';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Learn more about Firdavsbek Ismoilov, his background in software engineering, and the areas he focuses on professionally."
  path="/about/"
>
  <section class="section-shell">
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1 class="max-w-4xl text-5xl font-semibold text-slate-950 dark:text-white sm:text-6xl">
        Building dependable software, thoughtful developer experiences, and products that age well.
      </h1>
      <p class="max-w-3xl text-lg leading-8 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
        {siteConfig.author.name} is a software engineer who approaches product delivery with a
        systems mindset. He cares deeply about creating software that is maintainable under
        pressure, clear for teams to evolve, and practical for real users.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-shell mt-10 grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-[1.15fr_0.85fr]">
    <div class="surface space-y-6 px-6 py-8 md:px-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-slate-950 dark:text-white">Professional profile</h2>
      <p class="text-lg leading-8 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
        His background spans modern web engineering, backend integration, automation, and platform
        thinking. Rather than treating delivery as a handoff between disciplines, he tends to work
        across the full path from product intent to implementation details, helping teams connect
        architecture, user experience, and execution quality.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg leading-8 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
        He is especially motivated by software that supports long-term clarity: strong foundations,
        good defaults, readable abstractions, and tooling that reduces friction for the rest of the
        team. That means thinking not only about shipping features, but also about how systems are
        debugged, extended, documented, and operated over time.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg leading-8 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
        Beyond code, he values thoughtful communication, careful iteration, and craftsmanship.
        Whether the problem is frontend architecture, build pipelines, content systems, or a better
        authoring workflow, his focus is usually the same: make the next step easier, safer, and
        more reliable for both users and collaborators.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid gap-6">
      <div class="surface px-6 py-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-950 dark:text-white">Core strengths</h2>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-base leading-7 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
          <li>Designing maintainable web platforms and content-driven sites</li>
          <li>Improving developer workflows, automation, and release confidence</li>
          <li>Balancing product speed with code quality and operational stability</li>
          <li>Creating accessible, polished interfaces with strong information structure</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="surface px-6 py-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-950 dark:text-white">Focus areas</h2>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-base leading-7 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
          <li>Frontend systems and design implementation</li>
          <li>Static site architecture and performance-oriented builds</li>
          <li>Tooling, CI/CD, and workflow ergonomics</li>
          <li>Technical writing, documentation, and knowledge sharing</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="surface px-6 py-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-950 dark:text-white">Interests</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-7 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
          He enjoys exploring practical engineering tradeoffs, emerging developer tooling, AI-assisted
          workflows, and the design details that make technical products feel refined instead of merely
          functional.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
